Meet <b>Mimi</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Mimi lives at <a href='/home/?user=fryolla'>1088 Bear Mountain View</a>, in the classy neighborhood of Westridge. She has an excellent view of Bear Mountain from her home, and can often spot deer moving across it, especially during the winter (when they stand out against the snow).<br><br>This young lady is a very friendly, generous and insightful girl, who loves to hang out at the park with her friends. She is so thoughtful that, during visits to Peabody Park, she'll often pick up trash around the park and help keep it clean. Why, the mayor even awarded her with a trophy for helping to preserve the park's beauty.<br><br>When she isn't at the park, Mimi likes to walk around the mall with her friends, shopping for new music. Among her favorite types of music are classic rock, rhythm & blues, and classical. After a visit to the mall, she and her friends will often stop by the local pizza joint and share dinner.<br><br>When she isn't hanging out with her friends, Mimi will often enjoy more quiet activities, such as crossword puzzles and solving mysteries. She is a very clever girl, who has earned herself many scholastic trophies for her intelligence and performance in spelling bees and math competitions.<br><br>Mimi loves animals as well, and is often found gazing into a window of the local pet shop. She's already thinking of making a bed for a future pet, but she can't decide if she wants to make it green, magenta, or indigo, because those are all her favorite colors!<br><br>Mimi's most recent accomplishments include receiving a gold trophy for her participation in the Halloween Trick or Treat Extravaganza, and even more recently, getting 100% on the Millsberry Astronomy Challenge, which earned her a pair of goggles and an awesome new lab coat! Congratulations, Mimi!</div>
